.%20Slop%20is%20everywhere%20on%20the%20internet%2C%20but%20its%20most%20pure%20version%20exists%20on%20Facebook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbad-ai-art-is-overrunning-facebook-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShrimp%20Jesus%3C%2Fa%3E%20kind%20of%20slop%3A%20bizarre%2C%20obviously%20fake%2C%20and%20sometimes%20vaguely%20unsettling%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrypophobia-a-fear-of-holes-2015-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrypophobia-triggering%3C%2Fa%3E%20way.%20Common%20themes%20involve%20old%20people%20holding%20a%20birthday%20cake%20asking%20you%20to%20wish%20them%20a%20happy%20birthday%3B%20babies%20doing%20things%20babies%20shouldn't%20do%3B%20snakes%20eating%20buses%2C%20bikes%2C%20or%20other%20vehicles%20overloaded%20with%20hundreds%20of%20babies%20or%20some%20other%20cargo%3B%20soldiers%20with%20prosthetic%20legs%3B%20women%20with%20missing%20limbs%20and%20huge%20busts%3B%20and%20Jesus.%20The%20images%20are%20often%20sort%20of%20eerily%20exploitative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20tend%20to%20be%20posted%20on%20Facebook%20pages%20with%20generic-sounding%20names%20and%20captions%20that%20don't%20necessarily%20reflect%20the%20photo%2C%20like%20%26quot%3Bwhy%20don't%20photos%20like%20this%20ever%20trend%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bbeautiful%20cabin%20crew%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BScarlett%20Johansson%26quot%3B%20for%20an%20image%20of%20Jesus%20built%20into%20the%20hood%20of%20a%20car.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20slop%3F%20The%20best%20explanation%20is%20that%20the%20Facebook%20pages%20posting%20these%20are%20making%20bait%20for%20potential%20scam%20targets%2C%20helping%20scammers%20identify%20gullible%20people%20in%20the%20comments%20who%20they%20can%20potentially%20extract%20money%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20possibility%20is%20that%20posting%20these%20images%20is%20a%20good%20tactic%20to%20build%20up%20a%20large%20page%20audience%