oo%20long%20ago%2C%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook-ai-shrimp-jesus-zombie-internet-spam-content-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Especulated%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20why%20Meta%20hasn't%20cracked%20down%2C%20but%20considering%20nothing%20has%20seemed%20to%20change%2C%20I%20find%20myself%20wondering%20yet%20again%20%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22501fb8d8-1e46-4a8f-8576-8fae7a849914%5C%22%3EWhy%20doesn't%20Facebook%20just%20ban%20this%20slop%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20a%20few%20of%20my%20theories%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThese%20images%20don't%20technically%20violate%20any%20rules%20%E2%80%94%20no%20nudity%20or%20other%20forbidden%20imagery.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFacebook%20did%20make%20a%20warning%20label%20to%20note%20an%20image%20might%20be%20made%20with%20AI%20when%20its%20systems%20detect%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUsers%20actually%20enjoy%20this%20content%20%E2%80%94%20you%20see%20plenty%20of%20people%20in%20the%20comments%20who%20are%20probably%20duped%20and%20think%20it's%20a%20real%20image%2C%20or%20maybe%20just%20an%20interesting%20artistic%20rendition.%20Why%20mess%20with%20content%20people%20like%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFacebook%20does%20ban%20this%20stuff%2C%20but%20only%20at%20an%20account%20level%20when%20the%20account%20posting%20it%20engages%20in%20obvious%20spam%20tactics.%20But%20not%20all%20of%20the%20accounts%20are%20spamming.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESlop%20is%20often%20scam-adjacent%2C%20but%20the%20accounts%20posting%20it%20may%20not%20be%20directly%20always%20the%20ones%20doing%20the%20scams%2C%20so%20they%20don't%20get%20banned.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFacebook%20worries%20that%20banning%20this%20kind%20of%20AI%20content%20will%20set%20a%20bad%20precedent%20because%20it%20wants%20to%20encourage%20people%20to%20make%20stuff%20with%20its%20own%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-ai-llama-3-chatbot-mark-zuckerberg-existential-risks-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_bl