harset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667f02e3d1c84a0eaca8eada%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221359%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMultiple%20European%20arms%20makers%20are%20designing%20next-generation%20tanks%20like%20KNDS'%20Leclerc%20Evolution%2C%20seen%20at%20a%202024%20defense%20expo%20in%20Paris.%3Cp%3EArtur%20Widak%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20slew%20of%20new%20tank%20designs%20are%20emerging%20from%20European%20drawing%20boards.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMany%20are%20alternatives%20to%20the%20pan-European%20tank%20envisioned%20by%20France%20and%20Germany.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20faces%C2%A0domestic%20pressure%20to%20favor%20national%20projects%20that%20benefit%20a%20nation's%20workforce.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20the%20European%20tank%20market%20was%20fairly%20stable.%20Germany's%20Leopard%202%20was%20the%20most%20common%20model%20in%20European%20armies%2C%20with%20Britain%2C%20France%2C%20and%20Italy%20producing%20a%20small%20number%20of%20indigenous%20models%20for%20their%20own%20armies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20slew%20of%20new%20tank%20designs%20are%20emerging%20from%20European%20drawing%20boards.%20This%20is%20partly%20spurred%20by%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20which%20has%20seen%20the%20most%20intense%20armored%20warfare%20in%20Europe%20since%201945.%20But%20it%20may%20also%20reflect%20a%20lack%20of%20faith%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feuro-sd.com%2F2023%2F01%2Farticles%2F29122%2Fmain-ground-combat-system-mgcs-a-status-report%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMain%20Ground%20Combat%20System%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20joint%20project%20between%20France%20and%20Germany%20to%20develop%20a%20main%20battle%20tank%20by%202040.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20seems%20that%20every%20industrial%20partner%20is%20working%20on%20its%20own%20alternative%20to%20MGCS%2C%26quot%3B%20L%C3%A9o%20P%C3%A9ria-Peign%C3%A9%2C%20a%20French%20defense%20expert%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20inevitable%20that%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20tanks%20would%20emerge%20to%20replace%20the%20late%20Cold%20War%20designs%20that%20still%20dominate%20Western%20armies%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Leopard%202%2C%20M1%20Abrams%2C%20and%20Britain's%20Challenger.%20Even%20the%20US%20Army%20is%20aiming%20for%20a%20next-generation%20version%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defensenews.com%2Fland%2F2024%2F05%2F31%2Fa-lighter-high-tech-abrams-tank-is-taking-shape%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EM1%20Abrams%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20would%20slim%20down%20the%2070-ton%20behemoth%20to%20less%20than%2060%20tons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMCGS%20is%20meant%20to%20replace%20the%20Leopard%202%20and%20France's%20Leclerc%20as%20the%20primary%20tanks%20in%20the%20German%20and%20French%20armies.%20Both%20nations%20recently%20signed%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdsm.forecastinternational.com%2F2024%2F04%2F29%2Ffrance-and-germany-formalize-agreement-to-develop-future-main-battle-tank%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eagreement%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20begin%20development%20and%20manufacturing%20of%20a%20prototype.%20But%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20MGCS%20seemed%20like%20it%20might%20also%20replace%20the%20Leopard%202%20as%20a%20sort%20of%20pan-European%20tank.%20MGCS%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20a%20modular%20design%20with%20advanced%20features%20such%20as%20a%20140-mm%20gun%2C%20hybrid%20propulsion%2C%20advanced%20sensors%2C%20and%20the%20ability%20to%20team%20up%20unmanned%20ground%20vehicles.%20A%20conceptual%20model%20displayed%20in%202018%20used%20a%20Leopard%202%20hull%20and%20a%20Leclerc%20turret.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20are%20indications%20that%20Germany%20wants%20a%20fallback%20design%2C%20based%20on%20the%20latest%20Leopard%202A8%20model%2C%20in%20case%20MCGS%20fizzles%20out.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Leopard%202AX%2C%20an%20improved%20version%20of%20the%20Leopard%202A8%20battle%20tank%2C%20is%20being%20developed%20by%20the%20German%20defense%20industry%20at%20the%20express%20request%20of%20the%20Bundeswehr%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farmyrecognition.com%2Fnews%2Farmy-news%2Farmy-news-2024%2Fgermany-develops-next-gen-leopard-2ax-as-alternative-to-joint-mgcs-project-and-existing-leopard-2a8-tank%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArmy%20Recognition%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20defense%20news%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20development%20also%20serves%20as%20a%20Plan%20B%20for%20Germany%20in%20case%20of%20failure%20of%20the%20Franco-German%20program%2C%20or%20even%20as%20a%20lever%20in%20future%20negotiations%2C%20thus%20confronting%20France%20with%20a%20fait%20accompli%20regarding%20the%20crucial%20decisions%20that%20remain%20to%20be%20made%2C%26quot%3B%20Army%20Recognition%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20two%20new%20designs%20are%20being%20offered%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbreakingdefense.com%2F2024%2F06%2Fknds-unveils-new-leopard-and-leclerc-main-battle-tank-concepts%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKNDS%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20joint%20venture%20between%20German%20defense%20firm%20Krauss-Maffei%20Wegmann%20%E2%80%94%20manufacturer%20of%20the%20Leopard%202%20%E2%80%94%20and%20France's%20Nexter%2C%20which%20produces%20the%20Leclerc.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Leopard%202%20A-RC%203.0%20is%20a%20modular%20design%20with%20an%20unmanned%20turret%20with%20the%20crew%20nestled%20in%20the%20hull%2C%20similar%20to%20Russia's%20T-14%20Armata.%20It%20can%20fire%20guided%20missiles%20and%20heavy%20cannon%20rounds%2C%20plus%20it%20has%20a%2030-mm%20cannon%20and%20improved%20armor%20buttressed%20by%20an%20active%20protection%20system%20to%20stop%20anti-tank%20rockets.%20Existing%20Leopard%202%20models%20can%20also%20be%20fitted%20with%20these%20features.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESignificantly%2C%20KNDS%20%26quot%3Bassesses%20the%20Leopard%202%20A-RC%203.0%20not%20only%20as%20a%20bridge%20solution%20until%20introduction%20of%20the%20next-generation%20land%20combat%20system%20MGCS%2C%20but%20also%20as%20a%20decisive%20technological%20precursor%20to%20MGCS%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.knds.com%2Fnewsroom%2Fpress-releases%2Fdetail%2Fdefining-battlefield-superiority-knds-presents-groundbreaking-technologies-in-future-land-warfare%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompany%20press%20release%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKNDS%20is%20also%20touting%20the%20Leclerc%20Evolution%2C%20which%20is%20fitted%20with%20the%20company's%20Ascalon%20turret%20and%20gun.%20The%20company%20describes%20Ascalon%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20main%20gun%20for%20battle%20tanks%20that%20is%20more%20powerful%20than%20all%20comparable%20barrel%20weapons.%20It%20can%20fire%20compact%20and%20programmable%20ammunition%20beyond%20the%20line%20of%20sight%20with%20minimal%20wear.%20Due%20to%20its%20scalability%2C%20Ascalon%20can%20be%20fitted%20with%20any%20barrel%20from%20120%20to%20140%20mm.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20if%20the%20procurement%20picture%20wasn't%20complicated%20enough%2C%20four%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20KNDS%20Germany%2C%20KNDS%20France%2C%20Germany's%20Rheinmetall%20and%20France's%20Thales%20%E2%80%94%20have%20also%20just%20announced%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thalesgroup.com%2Fen%2Fworldwide%2Fdefence-and-security%2Fpress_release%2Findustry-signs-letter-intent-mgcs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejoint%20venture%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20develop%20the%20MGCS.%20Yet%20Rheinmetall%20is%20also%20marketing%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgerman-arms-maker-rheinmetall-offers-ukraine-new-panther-kf51-tank-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKF51%20Panther%3C%2Fa%3E%20tank%2C%20armed%20with%20a%20new%20130-mm%20cannon.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rheinmetall.com%2Fen%2Fmedia%2Fnews-watch%2Fnews%2F2023%2F12%2F2023-12-15-panther-developement-contract-hungary%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHungary%3C%2Fa%3E%20