0year%20and%20a%20half%20to%20earn%20that%20many%20Bonvoy%20points%2C%20but%20what%20better%20way%20to%20spend%20them%20than%20a%20relaxing%20tropical%20getaway%20just%20for%20the%20two%20of%20us%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20our%20flights%20cost%20a%20total%20of%2070%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-earn-and-redeem-delta-miles%5C%22%3EDelta%20miles%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20got%20a%20great%20deal%20on%20flights%20by%20booking%20six%20months%20in%20advance%20and%20being%20flexible%20on%20both%20travel%20days%20and%20flight%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBooking%20a%20weekday%20stay%20and%20opting%20for%20late%20or%20super-early%20flight%20times%20helped%20lower%20the%20cost.%20Once%20I'm%20on%20an%20airplane%2C%20my%20eyeshade%2C%20neck%20pillow%2C%20and%20white%20noise%20go%20on%2C%20so%20it%20doesn't%20matter%20too%20much%20that%20I'm%20missing%20out%20on%20sleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20hit%20the%20very%20start%20of%20the%20season%20in%20Cabo%2C%20which%20officially%20begins%20in%20April.%20Not%20traveling%20during%20the%20height%20of%20the%20season%20also%20helped%20keep%20total%20points%20cost%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20use%20our%20hotel%20card%20for%20everything%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20one%20comes%20with%20a%20huge%20caveat%20%E2%80%94%20only%20use%20your%20credit%20card%20for%20everyday%20purchases%20if%20you%20are%20committed%20to%20paying%20it%20off%20every%20single%20month.%20And%20I%20don't%20mean%20making%20one%20lump%20payment%20each%20month%20either%3B%20that%20can%20make%20it%20easy%20to%20overspend%20because%20your%20bank%20account%20looks%20temporarily%20inflated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20like%20to%20make%20credit%20card%20payments%20weekly.%20That%20way%2C%20you%20stay%20on%20track%20with%20paying%20off%20the%20balance%20in%20full%20each%20month.%20It%20helps%20you%20manage%20your%20inflow%20and%20outflow%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20bills%20and%20other%20direct%20debits%2C%20and%20paying%20it%20weekly%20really%20makes%20you%20feel%20the%20pain%2C%20as%20a%20friend%20of%20mine%20put%20it.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20it%20helps%20you%20still%20spend%20responsibly%2C%20even%20using%20a%20credit%20card.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20we%20moved%20almost%20all%20of%20our%20everyday%20spending%20to%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmarriott-bonvoy-boundless-credit-card-review%5C%22%3EMarriott%20Bonvoy%20Boundless%20Card%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20months%20leading%20up%20to%20our%20trip.%20With%20this%20card%2C%20you%20earn%20increased%20rewards%20on%20gas%20stations%2C%20grocery%20stores%2C%20and%20eating%20out%20%E2%80%94%20which%2C%20let's%20face%20it%2C%20was%20most%20of%20our%20spending%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20we%20didn't%20stop%20using%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-rewards-credit-cards%5C%22%3Erewards%20credit%20card%3C%2Fa%3E%20once%20we%20got%20there.%20We%20got%20a%20point%20multiplier%20on%20purchases%20at%20participating%20Marriott%20hotels%2C%20so%20even%20as%20we%20were%20enjoying%20one%20trip%2C%20we%20were%20already%20working%20toward%20the%20next%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20take%20advantage%20of%20work%20travel%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20pros%20and%20cons%20to%20one%20partner%20traveling%20weekly%20for%20business%20when%20you%20have%20kids.%20The%20cons%20are%20obvious%20%E2%80%94%20it%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20solo%20parent%2C%20the%20kids%20miss%20the%20parent%20whose%20travels%2C%20and%20you%20get%20less%20quality%20time%20as%20a%20family.%20But%20there%20are%20some%20positives%2C%20as%20well.%20For%20one%2C%20you%20make%20the%20most%20of%20the%20family%20time%20you%20do%20have.%20And%20importantly%2C%20the%20airline%20miles%20and%20hotel%20points%20stack%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20no%20idea%20when%20my%20husband%20started%20traveling%20several%20times%20a%20month%20that%20he'd%20be%20racking%20up%20as%20many%20airline